mosan_culture_group = {
	graphical_culture = northamericagfx
	#Note the Mosan division, one of Sapir's, is conclusively disproven as far as I'm concerned. Nevertheless, it is a
	#valid and feasible idea to put all these troublesome little one-culture-per-group cultures into a single group and
	#call it Mosan. Is extremely attractive from a gameplay and continuity point of view, and you can't exactly say they
	#were completely disimilar, sharing the same Sprachbund, habits, a bio region. Conversely, how much did the
	#Waskashans really share with the Inuit, or even Alutiq, possible very distant linguistic ties aside. And do we
	#really want Haida all by itself or shoved in with the Athabaskan supergroup. I can't imagine anyone would take
	#issue with this, unless it is to suggest adding Salishan to this group. That said, This a world class cultural
	#variety hotspot, so I'm going with Basque-like one-culture-per-group cultures here, at least for now. Old Mosan
	#idea repurposed into a Haida group, because internal code shenanigans =p.

	haida = {			#Language isolate. Formerly placed with Athabaskan, but this is accepted to be a mistake. Attempts have been made to place it with most other groups to limited success
		primary = HDA
		dynasty_names = {
			Kiusta Kung Yan Hiellan Skidegate "Cha'atl" Haina Kaisun Cumshewa Skedans Tanu Ninstints
			Masset Atewaas Jaahguhl Kayung "Hlk'yah GaawGa" Klinkwan Sukkwan Howkan Kasaan
		}
		male_names = {
			"Nanni Chaddi" "Na tio tish" Sitahle Oahtekah Ahzaah Kootzzah Moketaveto Ohtoahnesotowheo Harkkahome
			Munamenek Otoahnisto Mahvipah Choseta Nahtan Konzhontaco Bazheech Tillaka Chacon Dasoda-hae Cochise Juh
			Delshay Goyaale
		}
		female_names = {
			Dahteste Ilthgozay Gouyen Lozen Tohayea
		}
	}
}
